I think I saw a kit similar to this at the bus boys
website. http://www.busboys.com I had one of these in
my 71 deluxe. It worked good except the legs on the
seats cracked. I went through two rear seats because
of this problem.
Thanks,
Tyler
--- Richard Kerr <rich.kerr(-at-)verizon.net> wrote:
> In researching stuff for my '67 Microbus, I came
> across Z Products' Z-Bed
> conversion kit (www.zproducts.com). I was very
> interested in it, until later
> reading in the archive that they had stopped
> producing the kit. This kit is
> the only one I know of that lets you use the
> original back seat in a VW bus
> and convert it to a bed when desired, rather than
> installing a
> Westfalia-type camper Z-bed or a homemade
> convertible back "sofa." I like
> the idea of retaining the original look of my
> non-camper, but easily being
> able to camp, too.
> 
> Anyway, I was interested enough to call them today
> and plead, and I found
> out they do make them, but only when they have
> enough interest to run a
> batch. They told me that interest has dropped to the
> point where no batch
> has been run in a while. I replied that since many
> people believe they no
> longer make the kit, that may be why no one is
> calling or emailing to order.
> 
> For them, a batch is about thirty units (for any bus
> up to '79), not the
> half-dozen or so they presently have customer names
> for. I asked them to add
> my name to the list, and I wanted everyone on
> Vintagebus and Type2 to know
> that the product can be available if enough of us
> ask for it. I think it's
> an elegant solution for a non-camper conversion bus,
> and I have to believe
> there's enough interest out there to generate
> sufficient orders, once people
> realize that it is available and know exactly what
> it is.
> 
> Let them know if you're interested.
> 
> -- Rich
